#!/usr/bin/env bash

# Retired. Commit message reflowing is now a pre-commit commit-msg hook
# (utils/fmt-commit-msg), configured in .pre-commit-config.yaml and
# installed from the project_start repo. This wrapper, and its habit of
# saving and re-running the displaced hook, duplicated the check that
# pre-commit already runs.
#
# The script is kept only to explain itself: if a repository still has a
# commit-msg.legacy symlink pointing here, running it (as a management
# command or as a git hook) prints this note and fails.

set -eEuo pipefail

cat >&2 <<'EOF'
wrap-commit-msg has been retired.

Commit message reflowing is now handled by pre-commit as a commit-msg
hook (utils/fmt-commit-msg), configured in .pre-commit-config.yaml and
installed from the project_start repo.

If you are seeing this while committing, this repository still has a stale
commit-msg.legacy symlink pointing at this script. Migrate the repository
with:

    project-start <path-to-this-repo>

That removes the stale symlink and the saved commit-msg.d directory, and
installs the pre-commit hooks.
EOF

exit 1
